The paper discusses an analytical approach for steering complex systems towards a desired outcome, which involves building a complex network and determining minimal control configurations. This approach involves techniques from Fuzzy Cognitive Mapping (FCM) and network controllability, which are commonly used in the fields of systems and control engineering, artificial intelligence, and computational biology. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
